text: Gustave C. Haysler House is a historic home located at Clinton, Henry County, Missouri. It was built about 1896, and is two-story, Queen Anne style frame dwelling. It features steep hipped roofs, front porch with classical columns, and a cylindrical tower. (includes 13 photographs from 1994) It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1995. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Queen Anne architecture in Missouri Category:Houses completed in 1896 Category:Buildings and structures in Henry County, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Henry County, Missouri
